<br>
Actually that's not what I said.  What I said was to also remember that people may have some RP ideals that mean a /slight/ sacrifice in efficiency.<br>
<br>
A Shadow Knight can be a fine puller.  If that fits the SKs role and he is reasonably good at it should he NOT do it just because it doesn't fit the 'model?'<br>
<br>
When I played a Cleric I didn't melee.  I don't melee with my Wizard either.  But if I did and someone told me to stop being stupid and med I'd probably be somewhat offended.  No one is talking about having people go willy-nilly with Warriors insisting on being Main Healer with Bind Wounds.  What this thread has been discussing are the minutiae of Efficiency - I can see the next logical step being whether Warriors should Dual Wield or use 2HS.  One might be a tad better than the other in certain situations and with certain weapons, but on this server more than others I'd be tolerant of Personal Preference moreso than on other servers.<br>
<br>
Steeltoe - I do agree with many of your assessments, all I wished to add was the caveat that Fun has a place next to efficiency :-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/22/02 4:42:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=398.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Oh, you want general?</span><hr size=1> As a Druid who groups almost as often as he solos, I'd like to chime in here.<br>
<br>
First off, until yesterday, I didn't know about the stand-in-place thing, so you learn something new every day.<br>
<br>
In the groups I've been in, due to the relative paucity of clerics in our land, I tend to be the primary healer.  I understand my role is to sit back, meditate while everyone else does their thing, and heal people when they need it.  I'm pretty good at that, too.<br>
<br>
What I worry about, however, is how efficient my damage shields are and, even moreso, my damage over time spells are in group situations.  In the groups I've been in, unless things go very, very wrong (in which case I need all my mana for heals), monsters drop like flies.  If I put down a swarm spell, the monster's typically dead before it's gotten through even two or three tics.  I keep it memorized, and watch for opportunities to use it (as it seems to have a minimal aggro effect--much less than heals or direct damage blasts do), but I wonder if just tossing out a Careless Lightning when I want to do damage might be a better use of my mana.<br>
<br>
The same goes for the damage shield.  I use it habitually, and I know that it spreads the damage onto the monsters not being targetting, but the amount of damage, all things considered, is pretty minimal.<br>
<br>
Have faith that the members of your group know what they're doing.  Sometimes, appearances are deceptive.  I was in a group yesterday, getting pounded on by something, and I had myself targetted and was trying to put down a Shield of Barbs on myself.  One of my group members thought I was casting a root spell on a mesmerized monster, and some heated /tells ensued about my competency or lack thereof.   The casting visual effect of the Druidic Damage Shields is identical to the casting vidual effect of the root spells.<br>
<br>
Lastly, and I cannot stress this enough, if you let your healer go down, you're in a world of hurt, especially if there's only one in the group.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen Lothir<br>
