<br>
Oh, and an idea on the snare.  One of VI's famous tricks for making critters harder is to make them immune to magic when you're outside melee range.  The first MOB like this that most people encounter is the Ice Giant Diplomat in Permafrost (most dragons are like this, too).  However, perhaps they did it to smaller creatures on luclin. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.alienexplorer.com/clipart/images5/wolf.pawprint2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 224<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/23/02 1:36:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=398.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Effective roleplaying</span><hr size=1> Robin:<br>
